or OpenClaw/node on 18789** ⚠️\n\nThat combo often means it works locally but fails from another device.\n\n### Fast, safe fix (Private network only)\nRun PowerShell **as Administrator**:\n\n```powershell\nNew-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName \"OpenClaw Dashboard 18789 (Private)\" `\n  -Direction Inbound -Action Allow -Protocol TCP -LocalPort 18789 `\n  -Profile Private\n```\n\nThen test from phone/other device:\n`http://192.168.1.144:18789`\n\n### If still blocked after that\nThe router is likely isolating clients (guest/AP isolation).  \nI can guide you through checking that next.\n\nIf you want, say **“do it for me”** and I’ll apply/verify step-by-step.","textSignature":"msg_04ec897e4eeabb820169a36db533fc8191aae2d378879fcbd9"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":982,"output":304,"cacheRead":28160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29446,"cost":{"input":0.0017185,"output":0.004256,"cacheRead":0.004928,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0109025}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772318129812}}
